wikipedia_page.main: Corbett Eric Cresswell (3 August 1932 – 19 May 2017) was an English footballer who played as a centre half.

response: Warney's brother, Frank, also played for Sunderland as well as clubs including West Bromwich Albion, Chester and Notts County. His son, Corbett Cresswell, was in the Bishop Auckland team which won the FA Amateur Cup three years in succession in the 1950s. His great-granddaughter is Lincoln based Olympic swimmer Kate Haywood.
